# Acceptance gates must be reproducible + pinned + fail-fast

A gate is only worth trusting if it runs the same way every time and tells you loudly when it can't.
This rule exists because the editor CDP gate (`make leptos-gates`) once depended on unpinned external
state and **hung 130 s with a cryptic error** instead of failing fast — turning a routine ticket into a
multi-hour reverse-engineering session (T-177; root cause: `chrome-headless-shell` FATAL-crashing on
font fallback). Binds **every** agent (Claude Code, Cursor, Fable) and every human.

## Rules

1. **Reproducible + pinned.** A gate's external tools (browser, toolchain, DB image) are **pinned** and
   the pins are **committed and validated**, not floating dev-machine state. For the editor gate the
   pins live in [`tools/tbd-tools/gate-env.json`](../../tools/tbd-tools/gate-env.json) + root
   [`rust-toolchain.toml`](../../rust-toolchain.toml), validated by `gate doctor`. Bump a pin
   **deliberately, in the same commit** as the thing it pins.
2. **Fail-fast, never hang.** A gate that would wedge must fail in seconds with an **actionable
   message** (what's wrong + how to diagnose), not a multi-minute timeout. New browser/GPU gates get a
   preflight like `gate doctor` (a prerequisite of `make leptos-gates`).
3. **A gate that can't run is a P0 infra bug — fix the harness/env.** It is **never** a silent skip, a
   "commit anyway", or a "document as deferred" (see [`no-silent-deferrals.mdc`](no-silent-deferrals.mdc)).
   If you are truly blocked (missing GPU, secrets, Workbench down): STOP and ASK.
4. **New GPU/browser gates get CI or a scheduled lane.** Do not leave a gate "local per stream" forever
   — infra regressions must be caught by machines, not discovered mid-ticket. See
   [`editor-gates.yml`](../../.github/workflows/editor-gates.yml).
5. **When a gate breaks the environment, write it down.** Add/append a
   [`docs/platform/known-bugs/`](../../docs/platform/known-bugs/) entry and, for the editor gate, the
   [`EDITOR_GATE_RUNBOOK.md`](../../docs/website/EDITOR_GATE_RUNBOOK.md) so the next person doesn't
   re-derive it.
